# Secrets & Security

- NEVER hardcode credentials, API tokens, or passwords in source code
- NEVER commit files from `secrets/` or `.env` — they are in `.gitignore`
- Load sensitive values from environment variables or `.env` files using `python-dotenv`
- Database connection details come from env vars via `src/utils/db_connector.py`
- When showing example commands that include tokens, use placeholders like `<YOUR_API_TOKEN>`
